    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-08-18T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-08-18T18:00:00-05:00" n="652"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d652">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">357.AA/8–1850: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Acting United States Representative on the United Nations Commission for
                        Indonesia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Doolittle</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-08-18T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 18, 1950—7 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>182. Usgoc 470. For Doolittle.<note n="1" xml:id="d652fn1">Hooker A. Doolittle,
                        Foreign Service Reserve Officer with the rank of Minister, had replaced Dow
                        as the Acting United States Representative on the <gloss
                            target="#t_UNCIUNCFI1">UNCI</gloss>.</note> Dept understands <gloss
                        target="#t_UNCIUNCFI1">UNCI</gloss> offer of good offices to <gloss
                        target="#t_RI1">RI</gloss> in Ambon affair (<gloss target="#t_Embtel1"
                        >Embtel</gloss> 154, Aug 4, Gocus 877<note n="2" xml:id="d652fn2">Not
                        printed; it transmitted the text of a letter from the <gloss
                            target="#t_UNCIUNCFI1">UNCI</gloss> to Hatta expressing its readiness
                        and desire to lend any assistance or its good offices to the <gloss
                            target="#t_RUSI1">RUSI</gloss> Government. (357.AA/8–450)</note>) has
                    not yet been accepted. Also <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 171 Aug
                        8<note n="3" xml:id="d652fn3">Not printed.</note> indicates second Ambon
                    Peace Mission stalled with Lemeina still in Djakarta.</p>
                <p>Early settlement Ambon dispute particularly desirable since its continuance into
                    period of coming active negot re <gloss target="#t_NNG1">NNG</gloss> wld
                    decrease chances success.</p>
                <p>Dept therefore desires repeat suggestion included <gloss target="#t_Deptel1"
                        >Deptel</gloss> 168 Aug 6 that <gloss target="#t_UNCIUNCFI1">UNCI</gloss>
                    may wish consider using its still fresh success in Makassar as springboard
                    similar attempt Ambon.<note n="4" xml:id="d652fn4">Not printed. The <gloss
                            target="#t_UNCIUNCFI1">UNCI</gloss> had offered its good Offices to both
                        sides when the Dutch destroyer <hi rend="italic">Kortenaer</hi> had appeared
                        off Makassar without the approval of the Indonesian Government.</note>
                    Despite difficulty making <gloss target="#t_UNCIUNCFI1">UNCI</gloss> good
                    offices acceptable to <gloss target="#t_RI1">RI</gloss> owing <gloss
                        target="#t_RI1">RI</gloss> fear of implicit “recognition”, <pb facs="1068"
                        n="1054" xml:id="pg_1054"/> “South Moluccas Republic” Dept suggest <gloss
                        target="#t_MilEx1">MilEx</gloss> Board might be acceptable all parties.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
